01:47.674 --> 01:50.575
Even if I did,
you'd be wrong to believe me.

01:53.446 --> 01:54.470
Trust is a lie.

01:56.382 --> 01:57.815
Nobody ever knows anyone.

02:01.087 --> 02:04.181
<i>What does a young fellow like you</i>
<i>do for recreational activity?</i>

02:05.291 --> 02:08.282
<i>I like athletics,</i>
<i>horsing around with my pals.</i>

02:09.461 --> 02:12.625
<i>I suppose most of the fellows</i>
<i>like to chase girls.</i>

02:13.399 --> 02:17.859
<i>-And does that go for you, too?</i>
<i>-No, sir. I have a steady girl.</i>

02:19.139 --> 02:21.437
<i>Some kids find it difficult, having a steady.</i>

02:22.609 --> 02:25.203
<i>But I don't. I guess the key is...</i>

02:25.278 --> 02:27.838
<i>just finding someone who feels</i>
<i>the same way you do.</i>

02:32.018 --> 02:34.077
In 1955...

02:35.088 --> 02:39.491
students at Tree Hill High School
created a time capsule...

02:39.559 --> 02:42.050
that was to be opened in 50 years.

02:42.128 --> 02:44.562
They were simply asked
to talk about their lives.

02:46.232 --> 02:48.792
Isn't it interesting
how things haven't changed much?

02:50.136 --> 02:54.470
Within the next week, each of you will go
into our converted supply closet...

02:55.642 --> 02:59.476
push the green button in front of you,
and videotape your thoughts.

02:59.946 --> 03:01.743
-Do we have to?
-Yes, you have to.

03:02.982 --> 03:04.040
I won't see it.

03:04.484 --> 03:08.181
Nobody will. Not until 2055.

03:08.888 --> 03:11.482
By which time, I'll be dead and buried.

03:15.328 --> 03:17.023
-Nate, you got a second?
-No.

03:20.066 --> 03:21.465
Are you looking after him?

03:23.069 --> 03:24.195
I'm trying.

03:31.611 --> 03:32.839
I need to move out.

03:33.413 --> 03:34.402
What?

03:34.480 --> 03:37.574
-I'm gonna move back in with my folks.
-Why? Because we kissed?

03:38.618 --> 03:39.846
Yeah.

03:40.220 --> 03:43.212
-Okay, you know what?
-And I want to ask you out Friday night.

03:44.891 --> 03:47.086
I talked to Karen.
She agreed to watch Jenny.

03:48.027 --> 03:50.257
That's kind of presumptuous,
don't you think?

03:50.463 --> 03:51.953
I don't know. You tell me.

03:52.732 --> 03:54.165
And, by the way...

03:55.301 --> 03:57.861
you smell insanely good today.

04:03.843 --> 04:05.435
Friday night, 8:00.

04:06.646 --> 04:07.806
8:00.

04:15.888 --> 04:18.288
Okay, first off, I want to say...

04:18.358 --> 04:21.952
happy 67th birthday to Peyton Sawyer.

04:22.028 --> 04:23.962
You were pretty cool back in the day.

04:24.030 --> 04:27.363
To Jenny Jagielski who is...

04:29.569 --> 04:31.400
like, in her 50s now...

04:32.572 --> 04:34.096
your dad sure loves you.

04:35.908 --> 04:37.398
Plus, he's a total fox.

04:38.778 --> 04:40.609
I'm not going to let him outfox me.

04:42.382 --> 04:43.406
My lawyer called.

04:43.483 --> 04:46.646
The state requires a mediation
before they'll let me remove Lucas...

04:46.719 --> 04:47.845
from Dan's care.

04:50.023 --> 04:52.491
But you know what?
I'm not gonna let him rattle me.

04:52.925 --> 04:56.486
I will present my case
calmly and rationally...

04:57.563 --> 04:59.053
and let justice prevail.

05:00.433 --> 05:02.060
You're wise to use the system.

05:02.935 --> 05:05.130
But just in case, I made some calls.

05:07.106 --> 05:08.164
And?

05:08.241 --> 05:12.075
If Dan's the man I think he is,
my guy should have something soon.

05:16.849 --> 05:19.579
-What's up, Ms. President?
-Please, don't remind me.

05:19.652 --> 05:23.110
It was really fun to win and all,
but now I actually have to do something.

05:23.189 --> 05:24.520
What was I thinking?

05:24.590 --> 05:26.854
You were thinking
that you'd be great at this.

05:26.926 --> 05:30.293
Everyone who voted for you, including me,
was thinking the same thing.

05:32.432 --> 05:34.730
But I got you something.

05:35.401 --> 05:37.266
A present for the President.

05:37.637 --> 05:40.902
A present? Maybe this was a good idea.
What did I get?

05:41.641 --> 05:43.905
It's the book where I found
the quote for you.

05:45.211 --> 05:48.840
There's a lot of great stuff
on leadership in there.

05:49.482 --> 05:51.473
Lucas, thank you. It's perfect.

05:51.884 --> 05:53.818
I also thought you'd like these, too.

05:55.121 --> 05:58.579
I am so warming up
to being the President!

05:58.658 --> 06:00.148
There's my girl!

06:00.293 --> 06:03.353
Boyfriend! Hi. How was your cruise?

06:03.429 --> 06:06.091
It sucked. Wasted time away from you.

06:06.499 --> 06:08.126
Yeah, even the topless beach?

06:08.868 --> 06:11.200
Imagine the buzz kill
when I found my sister there.

06:14.540 --> 06:15.598
What's this?

06:15.675 --> 06:18.303
Lucas got me a gift
for being the president.

06:19.045 --> 06:20.205
A gift?

06:21.714 --> 06:24.080
I was gonna wait and surprise you,
but what the hell.

06:24.150 --> 06:26.880
I'm throwing my baby a party
to celebrate. Friday night.

06:27.420 --> 06:29.650
-A party with presents?
-You know it.

06:29.789 --> 06:32.155
I so love being the freaking President!

06:34.761 --> 06:37.889
Congrats again, Brooke. I'll see you later.

06:38.231 --> 06:39.289
Thanks, Lucas.

06:42.068 --> 06:44.730
Okay. I'll let you guys make out.

06:47.540 --> 06:49.337
My name is Anna Tagarro.

06:49.542 --> 06:51.510
And I'm a junior at Tree Hill High.

06:52.412 --> 06:55.279
And since it's 2055...

06:55.448 --> 06:57.143
I guess it's okay to say that...

06:58.751 --> 07:00.742
I'm bisexual.

07:03.356 --> 07:06.086
AIthough, if I still haven't
found the nerve to come out...

07:06.159 --> 07:09.128
to my friends and family by 2055....

07:11.431 --> 07:12.693
Surprise!

07:12.799 --> 07:13.788
Surprise.

07:16.335 --> 07:17.324
Keith?

07:18.671 --> 07:21.970
-What is this?
-This, my beautiful bride to be...

07:22.608 --> 07:23.734
is your new home.

07:24.710 --> 07:25.870
You bought a house?

07:27.413 --> 07:31.076
Keith, you can't just buy me a house.
This is too much.

07:31.150 --> 07:32.674
It's not too much.

07:34.020 --> 07:35.954
The truth is, it's not nearly enough.

07:38.524 --> 07:39.650
I love you, Jules.

07:43.496 --> 07:46.056
<i>Service department,please pick up Line 1.</i>

07:46.265 --> 07:47.527
Nate.

07:49.235 --> 07:50.224
How you been?

07:50.903 --> 07:53.736
Drunk. Bitter. Kind of like Mom.

07:58.744 --> 08:00.905
I want to apologize to you, Son.
Man to man.

08:02.682 --> 08:04.877
That was a hell of a punch
you hit me with.

08:06.519 --> 08:08.384
I guess I probably had it coming.

08:08.855 --> 08:09.844
Okay.

08:09.922 --> 08:13.858
Nate, don't shut me out, or your brother.

08:13.926 --> 08:16.087
Especially since
we're all working together now.

08:23.069 --> 08:25.560
Nice try, Dad. It's not that easy.

08:26.873 --> 08:27.897
I quit.

08:40.186 --> 08:42.245
My best friend Haley left town recently.

08:43.589 --> 08:44.783
And it's been hard.

08:48.127 --> 08:52.325
Until this year it's always been us
against the world.

08:52.965 --> 08:57.425
We pretty much grew up together
and now she's just gone.

09:00.640 --> 09:02.904
I understand the leaving part.

09:04.477 --> 09:05.569
Trust me.

09:08.214 --> 09:11.274
I just wish she would've called me
before she left.

09:12.585 --> 09:15.179
I wish I could have talked to her about it.

09:16.889 --> 09:18.254
Not to change her mind...

09:20.426 --> 09:21.757
or tell her what to do...

09:22.094 --> 09:25.962
but just to say, I love you.

09:27.466 --> 09:28.797
And I'll miss you.

09:32.071 --> 09:33.299
Just to say goodbye.

09:38.277 --> 09:39.505
Nathan?

09:42.181 --> 09:44.149
-What are you doing?
-Haley hates pink.

09:45.484 --> 09:46.883
Yeah. So?

09:50.790 --> 09:53.156
Nate, Haley's my best friend.

09:54.026 --> 09:58.520
I know it's not the same,
but I get what you're going through.

10:02.301 --> 10:03.700
-A clown.
-Yeah.

10:04.904 --> 10:06.132
They creep her out.

10:07.807 --> 10:09.968
-Man, you've got to call her.
-I did that.

10:11.377 --> 10:12.435
I got her voicemail.

10:12.712 --> 10:13.838
Voicemail.

10:14.347 --> 10:16.315
